        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The fender extension on both the driver and passenger side should be washed or wiped
                    clean of road dirt.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the fender extension on both sides of the vehicle for cracks.</para>
            </step1>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>If there are no cracks or if cracks only exist along the rear bottom edge of the fender
                        extension and do not extend beyond the 2 1/2 inch guideline shown in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f059041">Figure 1</hotlnk>, refer to Parts Information Table 1 for the
                        appropriate kit and TSI-05-09-01R for the Service Procedure.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If cracks exist along the rear bottom edge of the fender extension and extend beyond the 2 1/2
                        inch guideline shown in Figure 1 and / or other cracks are present, install a new fender
                        extension(s) (Table 2). Refer to Service Section S09008 for the Remove and Install Procedure and
                        Parts Information Table 1 for the appropriate fuel tank or fuel tank, air tank kit to be
                        installed.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
